	<title>Spring 2025 Midterm 1</title>
	<introduction>
		<p>
			<em>Notation:</em> <m>\mathbf{0}</m> denotes the zero vector, <m>O</m> denotes the zero matrix, and <m>I_{n}</m> denotes the <m>n\times n</m> identity matrix.
		</p>
	</introduction>
	<exercise points="8">
		<introduction>
			<p>
				Let <m>T:\mathbb{R}^{3}\to\mathbb{R}^{3}</m> by <m>T\left(\begin{bmatrix}x_{1}\\ x_{2}\\x_{3}\end{bmatrix}\right)=\begin{bmatrix}3x_{1}-x_{2}+2x_{3}\\ 2x_{1}\\ 2x_{1}+4x_{3}\end{bmatrix}</m>.
			</p>
		</introduction>
		<task workspace="1.5in" points="2">
			<statement>
				<p>
					Evaluate <m>T\left(\begin{bmatrix}3 \\1 \\2\end{bmatrix}\right)</m>.
				</p>
			</statement>
		</task>
		<task workspace="1.5in" points="2">
			<statement>
				<p>
					Find the (induced) matrix <m>A</m> such that <m>T(\mathbf{x})=A\mathbf{x}</m> for all <m>\mathbf{x}</m> in <m>\mathbb{R}^{3}</m>.
				</p>
		</statement>
	</task>
	<task workspace="3in" points="4">
		<statement>
			<p>
				Is there a <em>nonzero</em> vector <m>\mathbf{x}</m> in <m>\mathbb{R}^{3}</m> such that <m>T(\mathbf{x})=\begin{bmatrix}0\\ 0\\ 0\end{bmatrix}</m>? Fully justify your answer.
			</p>
		</statement>
	</task>
</exercise>
<exercise points="8">
	<introduction>
		<p>
			Suppose <m>A</m> is a <m>3\times 3</m> matrix and <m>\mathbf{u}=\begin{bmatrix}1 \\ -1\\1\end{bmatrix}</m> is an eigenvector of <m>A</m> corresponding to eigenvalue <m>-2</m>, and <m>\mathbf{v}=\begin{bmatrix}2 \\ 1 \\ 1\end{bmatrix}</m> is an eigenvector of <m>A</m> corresponding to eigenvalue <m>3</m>.
			Compute each of the following (note: your final answers will be vectors in <m>\mathbb{R}^{3}</m>).
			Show all work.
		</p>
	</introduction>
	<task workspace="1in">
		<statement>
			<p>
				<m>A\begin{bmatrix}4 \\ 2 \\ 2\end{bmatrix}=</m>
			</p>
		</statement>
	</task>
	<task workspace="1in">
		<statement>
			<p>
				<m>A^{3}\begin{bmatrix}1\\ -1 \\ 1\end{bmatrix}=</m>
			</p>
		</statement>
	</task>
	<task workspace="1in">
		<statement>
			<p>
				<m>A\begin{bmatrix}-1\\ -5 \\ 1\end{bmatrix}=</m>
			</p>
		</statement>
		<hint>
			<p>
				Can you write this vector as a linear combination of <m>\mathbf{u}</m> and <m>\mathbf{v}</m>?
			</p>
		</hint>
	</task>
</exercise>
